('w_environment_C2_13','isotopic fractionation','/ˌaɪsəˈtɒpɪk ˌfrækʃəˈneɪʃən/','noun phrase','동위원소 분별','The separation of isotopes in a chemical or physical process.','{Isotopic fractionation} helps scientists trace carbon sources.','동위원소 분별은 과학자들이 탄소 출처를 추적하는 데 도움을 줘요.','isotopic fractionation','C2','environment',1,'isotopic fractionation carbon science lab data'),
('w_environment_C2_14','Milankovitch cycle','/mɪˈlænkɒvɪtʃ ˈsaɪkəl/','noun phrase','밀란코비치 주기','Cycles in Earth''s orbital parameters that affect climate.','{Milankovitch cycles} explain ice age timing over millennia.','밀란코비치 주기는 수천 년에 걸친 빙하기 시기를 설명해요.','Milankovitch cycle','C2','environment',1,'Milankovitch cycle orbit earth ice age astronomy'),
('w_environment_C2_15','biogeography','/ˌbaɪoʊdʒiˈɒɡrəfi/','noun','생물지리학','The study of the distribution of species across the Earth.','{Biogeography} reveals how climate change shifts species ranges.','생물지리학은 기후 변화가 종의 분포 범위를 어떻게 바꾸는지 밝혀요.','biogeography','C2','environment',1,'biogeography map species distribution earth science'),
('w_environment_C2_16','anthrome','/ˈænθroʊm/','noun','인간 생태지역','A biome modified by long-term human activity.','Most of Earth''s land surface is now classified as {anthrome}.','지구 육지의 대부분이 이제 인간 생태지역으로 분류돼요.','anthrome','C2','environment',1,'anthrome human land ecology biome earth'),
('w_environment_C2_17','methanogenesis','/ˌmɛθənoʊˈdʒɛnɪsɪs/','noun','메탄 생성','The biological production of methane by archaea.','{Methanogenesis} in wetlands is a major natural methane source.','습지의 메탄 생성은 자연적 메탄의 주요 공급원이에요.','methanogenesis','C2','environment',1,'methanogenesis methane wetland microbe science'),
('w_environment_C2_18','dendroclimatology','/ˌdɛndroʊˌklaɪməˈtɒlədʒi/','noun','수목기후학','The study of past climate using tree ring data.','{Dendroclimatology} has reconstructed 1,000 years of temperature records.','수목기후학은 1,000년간의 기온 기록을 복원했어요.','dendroclimatology','C2','environment',1,'dendroclimatology tree ring data climate science'),
('w_environment_C2_19','xenobiotic','/ˌziːnoʊbaɪˈɒtɪk/','noun','이종생체물질','A chemical not normally found in an organism or ecosystem.','{Xenobiotics} such as pesticides accumulate in food chains.','살충제와 같은 이종생체물질이 먹이사슬에 축적돼요.','xenobiotic','C2','environment',1,'xenobiotic chemical pesticide food chain toxin'),
('w_environment_C2_20','geomorphology','/ˌdʒiːoʊmɔːrˈfɒlədʒi/','noun','지형학','The study of the physical features of Earth''s surface.','{Geomorphology} shows how climate shapes landscapes over time.','지형학은 기후가 시간에 따라 경관을 어떻게 형성하는지 보여줘요.','geomorphology','C2','environment',1,'geomorphology landscape earth rock erosion science'),
('w_environment_C2_21','limnology','/lɪmˈnɒlədʒi/','noun','호소학','The scientific study of freshwater lakes and ponds.','{Limnology} monitors water quality and ecosystem health.','호소학은 수질과 생태계 건강을 모니터링해요.','limnology','C2','environment',1,'limnology lake water freshwater science ecology'),
('w_environment_C2_22','photodegradation','/ˌfoʊtoʊdɛɡrəˈdeɪʃən/','noun','광분해','The breakdown of materials by light, especially sunlight.','{Photodegradation} breaks plastics into microplastics.','광분해는 플라스틱을 미세플라스틱으로 분해해요.','photodegradation','C2','environment',1,'photodegradation plastic sunlight UV science ocean'),
('w_environment_C2_23','carrying capacity','/ˈkæriɪŋ kəˈpæsɪti/','noun phrase','수용 능력','The maximum population size an environment can support.','Human activity has already exceeded Earth''s {carrying capacity}.','인간 활동은 이미 지구의 수용 능력을 초과했어요.','carrying capacity','C2','environment',1,'carrying capacity population earth resource limit'),
('w_environment_C2_24','stoichiometry','/ˌstɔɪkiˈɒmɪtri/','noun','양론','The calculation of quantities in chemical reactions in ecosystems.','{Stoichiometry} explains nutrient cycling imbalances in ecosystems.','양론은 생태계의 영양 순환 불균형을 설명해요.','stoichiometry','C2','environment',1,'stoichiometry chemistry nutrient cycle ecosystem science'),
('w_environment_C2_25','macroecology','/ˌmækroʊɪˈkɒlədʒi/','noun','거시 생태학','The study of large-scale patterns in the distribution of organisms.','{Macroecology} reveals how climate controls biodiversity.','거시 생태학은 기후가 생물 다양성을 어떻게 조절하는지 밝혀요.','macroecology','C2','environment',1,'macroecology pattern species global climate data'),
('w_environment_C2_26','exergy','/ˈɛksɜːrdʒi/','noun','엑서지','The maximum useful work obtainable from a system in a given environment.','{Exergy} analysis optimises energy use in industrial processes.','엑서지 분석은 산업 공정에서의 에너지 사용을 최적화해요.','exergy','C2','environment',1,'exergy energy efficiency thermodynamics industry'),
('w_environment_C2_27','palaeoecology','/ˌpæliɔɪˈkɒlədʒi/','noun','고생태학','The study of ancient ecosystems using fossil evidence.','{Palaeoecology} reconstructs how past species responded to climate change.','고생태학은 과거 종이 기후 변화에 어떻게 반응했는지 재구성해요.','palaeoecology','C2','environment',1,'palaeoecology fossil ancient ecosystem science history'),
('w_environment_C2_28','abiogenesis','/ˌeɪbaɪoʊˈdʒɛnɪsɪs/','noun','무생물 생성','The natural process by which life arises from non-living matter.','{Abiogenesis} is studied to understand early Earth conditions.','무생물 생성은 초기 지구 환경을 이해하기 위해 연구돼요.','abiogenesis','C2','environment',1,'abiogenesis origin life earth science chemistry'),
('w_environment_C2_29','endosymbiosis','/ˌɛndoʊsɪmˈbaɪoʊsɪs/','noun','세포내 공생','A relationship where one organism lives inside another.','{Endosymbiosis} explains the origin of chloroplasts in plants.','세포내 공생은 식물의 엽록체 기원을 설명해요.','endosymbiosis','C2','environment',1,'endosymbiosis cell biology chloroplast evolution'),
('w_environment_C2_30','photochemical smog','/ˌfoʊtoʊˈkɛmɪkəl smɒɡ/','noun phrase','광화학 스모그','Smog formed by sunlight reacting with air pollutants.','{Photochemical smog} is a serious health hazard in many cities.','광화학 스모그는 많은 도시에서 심각한 건강 위협이에요.','photochemical smog','C2','environment',1,'photochemical smog city air pollution health'),
('w_environment_C2_31','volatile organic compound','/ˈvɒlətaɪl ɔːrˈɡænɪk ˈkɒmpaʊnd/','noun phrase','휘발성 유기 화합물','Chemicals that evaporate at room temperature and pollute the air.','{Volatile organic compounds} from paints worsen indoor air quality.','페인트의 휘발성 유기 화합물은 실내 공기 질을 악화시켜요.','volatile organic compound','C2','environment',1,'volatile organic compound paint air indoor health'),
('w_environment_C2_32','coccolithophore','/ˌkɒkəlɪˈθɒfɔːr/','noun','원석조류','Tiny marine algae that produce calcium carbonate plates.','{Coccolithophores} are sensitive indicators of ocean acidification.','원석조류는 해양 산성화의 민감한 지표예요.','coccolithophore','C2','environment',1,'coccolithophore ocean marine algae acid micro'),
('w_environment_C2_33','negative emissions technology','/ˈnɛɡətɪv ɪˈmɪʃənz tɛkˈnɒlədʒi/','noun phrase','네거티브 배출 기술','Technology that removes CO2 from the atmosphere.','{Negative emissions technologies} include direct air capture.','네거티브 배출 기술에는 직접 공기 포집이 포함돼요.','negative emissions technology','C2','environment',1,'negative emissions technology CO2 capture climate'),
('w_environment_C2_34','Earth system science','/ɜːrθ ˈsɪstəm saɪəns/','noun phrase','지구 시스템 과학','The study of Earth as a set of interacting physical, chemical, and biological systems.','{Earth system science} integrates climate, ecology, and geology.','지구 시스템 과학은 기후, 생태학, 지질학을 통합해요.','Earth system science','C2','environment',1,'earth system science climate ecology geology'),
('w_environment_C2_35','refugium','/rɪˈfjuːdʒiəm/','noun','피난처','An area where species survive during adverse environmental conditions.','{Refugia} allow species to persist through climate change.','피난처는 기후 변화 속에서 종이 살아남을 수 있게 해줘요.','refugium','C2','environment',1,'refugium species habitat climate refuge nature');

